snippet.textDisplay:
The chirpy part describes the chaos and stress of managing a wedding, guests, impressing the groom’s family etc

The melancholic part, on the other hand, is essentially describing the bride’s beauty and the father blessing his daughter

So the chirpy-bubbly part is a description of a stressful situation while the melancholic sounding part is actually a description of beauty and blessing

In the middle, the song includes the bride’s perspective. The saddest part. Where she’s essentially thinking of all the rules she’ll have to follow at her marital place (dressing, presenting herself), all the letters addressed to her won’t reach her because her address (and name) would change, essentially thinking of her destiny as she leaves her childhood home. Later, the father wishes that the god will protect her childlike innocence. 

Such an amazing amalgamation of sadness and happiness… something that a wedding is. It works wonders. You may say that Coke Studio Pakistan or Bangla are doing a better job, and I’d mostly agree. 

But this one’s special. For me, this might be amongst the best songs I’ve ever heard. Let alone Coke Studio (India/Bangla/Pak/Tamil/Any country/language) songs. 

Such beauty ❤😭
